title: Shadows 14
body:
(Decisions Excerpt)

He prided himself on not sobbing like a baby through the emotional process, but it still didn’t stop him from curling up on her bed, about a couple of hours later, and staring at the large plushie wolf she had fondly called Nymeria.

“She should have taken you with her,” he whispered to the unblinking stuffed animal, before poking its stomach gently. “I bet she misses you like crazy.”

Just as I do…every fucking minute…

He had no idea when he dozed off, though he would vacantly recall his dreams being filled with running through the Wolfswood forest with a stuffed Ghost and Nymeria chasing after him, while Arya was dressed in a mixed martial arts outfit punching what appeared to be a giant effigy of a bear. Dany had just appeared as a naked nymph beckoning him for a quickie – on the Wall of all places - when the sudden loud banging from inside his head had him wincing in dismay.

Just a quickie, he’d beg as he willed the rapidly dissipating vision of Dany to remain in his subconscious. Unfortunately, the loud banging would continue incessantly until he lifted his lashes and groaned into the pillow.

What…the…?

“Jon? You in here?”

Ty…Tyrion?!

Continue on AO3

Much thanks and appreciation to @annagreengrass for always coming through with the fabulous mood boards!

summary:
Kerry Ford
 and Darren Prew married in June 2014 in a Game of Thrones-inspired wedding at Eastnor Castle in Herefordshire,...
caption:
Kerry Ford and Darren Prew married in June 2014 in a Game of Thrones-inspired wedding at Eastnor Castle in Herefordshire, England. The couple won a contest held by Blinkbox to mark the release of season four of the show. Kerry, Darren, and their guests were transformed into various characters from the show by a team of professional hair stylists and make-up artists. Kerry dressed as Queen Daenerys Targaryen and Darren as Jon Snow.

Photos from Blinkbox (top, middle left, middle right, bottom).

summary: Do you think something important near the end is going to hinge on two or more Starks having total blind faith in their family...
question: Do you think something important near the end is going to hinge on two or more Starks having total blind faith in their family bonds and making a giant leap trusting that a sibling is not going betray them? Because that might explain what the show writers were thinking with Sansa & Arya, like they were conscious of the thing where Sansa would never be afraid of Arya & Arya would never think Sansa was trying to elevate herself at the cost of Jon/Bran, but they didn't bother showing that on screen
answer:
I think Stark teamwork and love is going to be vital to the end of the series, yes. They’ve been kept apart so long so that it matters when they get back together, both emotionally and to how the external conflict plays out; Sansa, Arya, and Bran in particular have been getting training montages in three distinct and complementary skillsets. They can do more together than any of them can do apart.

I don’t think highly of how the show’s written Stark relationships in the past few seasons. The constant infighting and hostility, with so little justification, has displayed a real poverty of imagination.
